// Test fixture for task 4744 (mesh-morph producer hook + morph-or-remesh arm, β).
//
// Mirrors the α VolumeMesh-demand probe shape (volume_mesh_box.ri): `vm_probe`
// is an @optimized("test::vm-demand-probe") consumer returning a NON-geometry
// type (Int) so `let probe = vm_probe(body)` is a value_cell the module-static
// VolumeMesh-demand pass can see (a Geometry-typed consumer would lower to a
// separate realization and be invisible). The engine registers the probe demand
// + the morph producer in the e2e.
//
// NON-structural morph lever: `width`/`depth`/`height` (continuous Length) scale
// the box while preserving face/edge/vertex topology — a tick keeps morph
// ELIGIBLE (full face/edge/vertex bijection → morphed, connectivity preserved).
//
// The body is a PLAIN `box(...)` primitive (NOT a boolean). When a morph
// producer is registered the dispatch forces the task-4092 *attributed* gmsh
// meshing path on (so the source mesh carries a `BoundaryAssociation` the morph
// projects through). That path reconstructs the B-rep topology at a 45° feature
// angle so tetgen can recover corners/edges/faces — a clean primitive box
// tessellates cleanly there, whereas a boolean-derived B-rep (e.g.
// `difference(box, cyl)`) leaves coplanar/seam triangulation that crashes
// tetgen's boundary recovery (`recoveredgebyflips`). So the morph e2e uses a
// primitive box exactly like the α fixture, which already proves a plain `box`
// body lowers to its own terminal realization read back by `vm_probe(body)`.
//
// The STRUCTURAL morph lever (a topology-changing param → morph Ineligible
// CountMismatch → remesh) lives in an INLINE fixture inside step-21's
// `e2e_structural_tick_remeshes_and_records_ineligible` (morph_arm_e2e.rs) — a
// box minus a movable cutter. It is kept out of THIS shared fixture so the live
// `e2e_no_producer_engine_remeshes_volume_mesh` foundation test keeps a clean,
// proven plain box (the boundary-demanding structural e2e is #[ignore]d on
// #4876 regardless, so a shared structural fixture would buy nothing).

@optimized("test::vm-demand-probe")
fn vm_probe(g: Geometry) -> Int {
    0
}

structure MorphBox {
    param width: Length = 10mm
    param depth: Length = 10mm
    param height: Length = 10mm

    let body = box(width, depth, height)
    let probe = vm_probe(body)
}
